						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 815, Pramāthi (= A.D. 893-94),</hi> and pertains to the reign of the Rāshṭrakūṭa king <hi rend="bold">Akālavarsha Śubhatuṅga-Bhaṭāra</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Kṛishṇa II). The <hi rend="italic">Mahāsāmanta</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kaṇṇa,</hi> who is said to have been ruling over <hi rend="bold">Sindavāḍi one-thousand,</hi> granted to <hi rend="bold">Śive-Nāyaka</hi> some <hi rend="italic">sthiti</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Maṁchāḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
